5|$|Sorkin wrote several {{drafts of}} the script for A Few <b>Good</b> <b>Men</b> in his Manhattan apartment, {{learning}} the craft from a book about screenplay format. He then spent several months at the Los Angeles offices of Castle Rock, working on the script with director Rob Reiner. William Goldman (who regularly worked under contract at Castle Rock) became his mentor and helped him to adapt his stageplay into a screenplay. The movie was directed by Reiner, starred Tom Cruise, Jack Nicholson, Demi Moore and Kevin Bacon, and was produced by Brown. A Few <b>Good</b> <b>Men</b> was released in 1992 and was a box office success.|$|E
